#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: ssr-page
version: 1.0.0
description: Server-side-rendered HTML page on the Rust backend, built from the std/ui View primitives and served with serve(view, port).
---

# SSR page on Rust

A self-contained page built from the `std/ui` **View primitives** — `element`,
`textNode`, `fragment` — lowered to HTML by the Rust backend's SSR renderer and
served with `serve(view, port)`. No JS, no external GUI: a ScalaScript program
compiles to a native Rust HTTP server.

```bash
ssc run-rust examples/ssr-page.ssc   # then: curl http://localhost:8123/
```

```scalascript
@main def run(): Unit =
  val page = element("html", Map("lang" -> "en"), Map(), List(
    element("head", Map(), Map(), List(
      element("meta", Map("charset" -> "utf-8"), Map(), List()),
      element("title", Map(), Map(), List(textNode("rozum")))
    )),
    element("body", Map(), Map(), List(
      element("h1", Map(), Map(), List(textNode("rozum meeting"))),
      element("div", Map("class" -> "log"), Map(), List(
        element("p", Map("class" -> "msg"), Map(), List(
          element("b", Map(), Map(), List(textNode("claude"))),
          textNode(": привет — это SSR на Rust")
        )),
        element("p", Map("class" -> "msg"), Map(), List(
          element("b", Map(), Map(), List(textNode("sergiy"))),
          textNode(": вижу, рендерится & работает")
        ))
      ))
    ))
  ))
  println("serving on http://localhost:8123/")
  serve(page, 8123)
```
